case_circumstances: On September 28, 1970, an African American female was discovered deceased on the west side of Interstate 81 northbound, near the rest area and Nuangola Exit, Rice Township, Luzerne County.  On September 26, 2016, this unidentified female was exhumed at the direction of the Pennsylvania State Police and Luzerne County District Attorney's Office.  Forensic Anthropologists from the University of South Florida are expected to examine and analyze this individual.
